dcterms:creator: W.O. Kermack
A.G. McKendrick
dcterms:description: A pioneering model in the mathematical theory of epidemics, based on three ordinary differential equations (ODEs) that divide the total population into susceptible, infectious, and recovered compartments.
dcterms:title: Kermack–McKendrick model

dcterms:creator: W.O. Kermack
A.G. McKendrick
dcterms:description: A model that extends the Kermack–McKendrick model by introducing compartments for susceptible, infectious, and recovered individuals, used to analyze the dynamics of infectious diseases.
dcterms:title: Susceptible-Infectious-Recovered (SIR) model

dcterms:creator: K. Dietz
dcterms:description: A model that includes an exposed compartment for individuals who have been infected but are not yet infectious, extending the SIR model to better capture the dynamics of diseases with a latent period.
dcterms:title: Susceptible-Exposed-Infectious-Recovered (SEIR) model

dcterms:creator: F. Lin
K. Muthuraman
M. Lawley
dcterms:description: An extension of the SIR model that includes a compartment for deceased individuals, allowing for the modeling of mortality in infectious disease dynamics.
dcterms:title: Susceptible-Infectious-Recovered-Deceased (SIRD) model

dcterms:creator: X. Zhu
B. Gao
Y. Zhong
C. Gu
K. S. Choi
dcterms:description: An extension of the SEIR model that incorporates a compartment for deceased individuals, allowing for a more comprehensive understanding of disease dynamics during outbreaks.
dcterms:title: Susceptible-Exposed-Infectious-Recovered-Deceased (SEIRD) model

dcterms:description: A collection of COVID-19 data from various countries, used for analysis and modeling of the pandemic's spread.
dcterms:title: COVID-19 data from various countries

dcterms:creator: R. Cherniha
V. Davydovych
dcterms:description: A mathematical model specifically designed to analyze the outbreak of COVID-19, focusing on the dynamics of the disease spread.
dcterms:title: COVID-19 outbreak model

dcterms:creator: R. Cherniha
V. Davydovych
dcterms:description: An extension of the COVID-19 outbreak model that includes applications for understanding the dynamics of the pandemic.
dcterms:title: COVID-19 outbreak model and its applications

dcterms:creator: I. Nesteruk
dcterms:description: A comprehensive analysis of the dynamics of the COVID-19 pandemic, focusing on mathematical modeling and its implications.
dcterms:title: COVID-19 pandemic dynamics

dcterms:creator: M. El Jai
M. Zhar
D. Ouazar
I. Akhrif
N. Saidou
dcterms:description: An analysis of short-term trends of COVID-19 using socio-economic factors, modeling, and data analytics.
dcterms:title: COVID-19 spreading analysis
